# Task Output Configuration

Controls where `/schedule` pushes confirmed tasks after saving to TASKS.md.
Edit this file to switch adapters or change target list/project settings.

---

## Plugin Root

plugin_root: ~/repos/claude-eisenhower

---

## Active Adapter

reminders

---

## Adapter Settings

### reminders
list_name: YOUR_REMINDERS_LIST_NAME

### asana (future)
workspace_id: ~~asana_workspace
project_id:   ~~asana_project

### jira (future)
base_url:    ~~jira_url
project_key: ~~jira_project

### linear (future)
team_id:     ~~linear_team
project_id:  ~~linear_project

---

## How to Set Up

1. Copy this file: `cp task-output-config.md.example task-output-config.md`
2. Set `plugin_root` to the absolute path where this plugin is installed.
   Default is `~/repos/claude-eisenhower` — update if you cloned elsewhere.
3. Set `list_name` under `### reminders` to the name of your Reminders list.
   It will be created automatically if it doesn't exist.
4. The actual `task-output-config.md` is gitignored — never committed.

## How to Switch Adapters

1. Install the MCP connector for the new system via Cowork plugin settings
2. Create `adapters/[system].md` following the interface in `adapters/README.md`
3. Change `Active Adapter` above to the new adapter name (e.g., `asana`)
4. Fill in the adapter-specific settings under the matching `### [system]` block
5. No changes needed to `commands/schedule.md` or any skill files

See `adapters/README.md` for the full adapter contract.
